{"lemma":"عَدْوِ","slug":"عَدْوِ","root":"ع.د.#","root_slug":"ع-د-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-د-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَدْو","root":"عدو","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28376","n28377","n28393"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%92%D9%88%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"enemy; foe","examples":[{"text":"الْأَخِلَّاءُ يَوْمَئِذٍ بَعْضُهُمْ لِبَعْضٍ عَدُوٌّ إِلَّا الْمُتَّقِينَ","english":"Close friends, that Day, will be enemies to each other, except for the righteous."},{"text":"هُمُ ٱلْعَدُوُّ فَٱحْذَرْهُمْ","english":"They are the enemy, so beware of them."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕa.duww/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28376","headword_ar":"عَدْوٌ","root":"Edw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. of 1 [q. v.] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEala ka*aA EadowFA","text_ar":"فَعَلَ كَذَا عَدْوًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badowFA","text_ar":"بَدْوًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did thus openly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"publicly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n28377","headword_ar":"عِدْوٌ","root":"Edw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EidFY","text_ar":"عِدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA='N","text_ar":"عَدَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n28393","headword_ar":"عَدُوٌّ","root":"Edw","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And enemy, contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waliY~N","text_ar":"وَلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadiyqN","text_ar":"صَدِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadiyqN muwaAlK","text_ar":"صَدِيقٌ مُوَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) an epithet, but resembling a subst.: (S:) [and (like our word “ enemy ” in military parlance)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hostile party:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] it is used alike as sing. and pl. and masc. and fem.; (Msb, K;) as is said in the “ Muk- tasar el-' Eyn: ” (Msb:) but sometimes it is dualized and pluralized and feminized: (K:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEodaA='N","text_ar":"اَعْدَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEodaA='N","text_ar":"اَعْدَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEaAdK","text_ar":"اَعَادٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, K; *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EidFY","text_ar":"عِدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EudFY","text_ar":"عُدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"are also pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaduw~N","text_ar":"عَدُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K; [each improperly termed in the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisomu jamoEK","text_ar":"اِسْمُ جَمْعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEalN","text_ar":"فِعَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEalN","text_ar":"فُعَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are measures of pls., not of quasi-pl. ns.;]) the former said by ISk to be the only pl. of this measure among epithets; (S, Msb; *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EudaApN","text_ar":"عُدَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm and with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", is another pl.; (Th, S, Msb;) and is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAdK","text_ar":"عَادٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaduw~N","text_ar":"عَدُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K, TA;) as in the saying of a woman of the Arabs,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$omata rab~u AlEaAlamiyna EaAdiyaka","text_ar":"اَشْمَتَ رَبُّ العَالَمِينَ عَادِيَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May the Lord of the beings of the universe make thy enemy to rejoice at thy affliction"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, TA:) the fem. form of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaduw~N","text_ar":"عَدُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaduw~apN","text_ar":"عَدُوَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) which is said by Az to be used when the meaning of an epithet is intended: (Msb:) it is said by ISk, (S, TA,) and in the “ Bari', ” (Msb,) that there is no instance of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEuwlN","text_ar":"فَعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEilN","text_ar":"فَاعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"but its fem. is without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaduw~apN","text_ar":"عَدُوَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi Eaduw~apN A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ عَدُوَّةٌ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This"},{"kind":"text","text":"woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is the enemy of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: accord. to Fr,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaduw~apN","text_ar":"عَدُوَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has the affix"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"to assimilate it to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadiyqapN","text_ar":"صَدِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for a word is sometimes formed to accord with its contr.: (S, TA:) AZ says that he heard certain of the tribe of 'Okeyl say, [of some women,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hun~a waliy~aAtu A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"هُنَّ وَلِيَّاتُ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaduw~aAtu A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"عَدُوَّاتُ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^FwoliyaAw^uhu","text_ar":"اًوْلِيَاوُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEodaAw^uhu","text_ar":"اَعْدَاوُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are the friends of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the enemies of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) [The pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EidFY","text_ar":"عِدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Persons distant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remote, one from another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, K, TA:) and (K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strangers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foreigners:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, K, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as are distant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remote, in respect of relationship;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not relations:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) as well as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enemies:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAlA^aEodaA='i","text_ar":"كَالاَعْدَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is added in the K after"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlgurabaA='u","text_ar":"وَالغُرَبَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", should be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlA^aEodaA='u","text_ar":"وَالاَعْدَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Msb","TA","ISd","ISk","M"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}